article.headline: TCU 58, Wyoming 52
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas -- Craig Williams scored 13 points and TCU used a 14-2 second-half run to defeat Wyoming 58-52 on Wednesday night. Hank Thorns added 12 points and Amric Fields came off the bench to score 10 for the Horned Frogs (13-8, 3-3 Mountain West). TCU trailed 46-45 with 15 minutes left before scoring 14 points in the next six minutes while holding the Cowboys to one field goal. Leonard Washington led Wyoming (17-5, 3-3) with 21 points. Adam Waddell had 13 points and a game-high nine rebounds for the Cowboys, and Francisco Cruz scored 10 points. TCU shot 46 percent from the field and had 20 points from its reserves while Wyoming got none. The Cowboys shot 32 percent from the field.
